Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Fill and boil your #kettle{} to re-hydrate the sun-dried tomatoes. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @Echalion shallot{1}. Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125}. Slice the @Tenderstem broccoli{150} in half widthways. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Pop the @sun-dried tomatoes{30} in a #bowl{} and cover completely with boiling water. Set to one side to re-hydrate for ~{12-15%minutes}, then drain in a #sieve{} and roughly chop.

Meanwhile, pop the baby plum tomatoes and tenderstem broccoli onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{} and sprinkle over a pinch of @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Toss to coat everything in the oil then pop onto the top shelf of the oven to cook until the tomatoes have softened and the broccoli has roasted, ~{15%minutes}.

In the meantime, put a good glug of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. When hot, add the @gnocchi{400}. Cook until golden and crispy, ~{8-10%minutes}. Stir to turn the gnocchi occasionally so they colour evenly. Once nicely golden, transfer the gnocchi to a bowl. Keep the pan!

Add another drizzle of @oil{} (and a good knob of @?butter{}) to your now empty frying pan and place over medium heat. Once hot, add the shallot and cook until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}, stirring regularly. Once soft, stir in the garlic, drained sun-dried tomatoes and a pinch of @chilli flakes{1/2%tsp}. Cook, stirring, for ~{30%seconds}. Remove from the heat.

Next, mix the roasted vegetables, half the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40} and the @green pesto{45}(use as much as you would like!) into the shallot mixture. Tip the gnocchi back into the pan and gently stir to coat. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

Divide the gnocchi up into large #bowls{} and sprinkle over the remaining hard Italian cheese and another pinch of chilli flakes if you would like! Enjoy!

> We love good Pesto and Tomato Gnocchi and this deliciously simple, chef-curated recipe doesn't disappoint. Time to bust out the pots and pans!